npx playwright test tests/<file-name>

⚖️ Key Difference
Getter form (locator.textContent()) → returns the actual string value.
Assertion form (expect(locator).toHaveText("...") or regex) → verifies the text matches what you expect.

✅ Summary:
textContent() → get the text.
textContent("A") → check text equals "A".
textContent(/A/i) → check text matches regex (contains “A”, case‑insensitive).

.all()  -- this method returns a promise that resolves to a list of all elements matching the locator.



