Hooks in Playwright 
test.beforeAll(Async(){
    //code you want to execute before all the tests  -- launch the browser
})

test.afterAll(Async(){
    //code you want to execute after all the tests  - close the browser
})

test.beforeEach(Async(){
    //code you want to execute before each tests  -- Launch URL
})
test.afterEach(Async(){
    //code you want to execute after each tests  -- Completion
})

beforeAll  - Runs once before all tests
afterAll - Runs once after all tests
beforeEach = Runs before each tests
afterEach - Runs after each tests


-->
Annotations are special methods in playwright, its lebel or instruction which tells what to execute and what not to
test.describe -> Groups related tests
test.skip -> skips the test, 
test.only -> runs only this tests, ignores others

test.fixme -> Marks a test as expected to fail, Temporarily ignoring a broken test
test.slow -> marks a test as slow , running a slow test, (eg heavy UI interaction) 
test.fail -> marking known bug as expected ti fail


