Allure report
npm install -D allure-playwright
['allure-playwright'],
allure generate allure-results --clean -o allure-report
allure open allure-report

what is allure report in playwright
In Playwright, Allure Report is a popular reporting framework that integrates with your test runs to produce rich, interactive reports. It’s not built into Playwright itself, but you can configure it with Playwright Test to get detailed insights into your automation results.

🌟 What Allure Report Provides
Visual test results: A web-based dashboard showing passed, failed, skipped tests.
Step-by-step logs: Each action (like page.goto, click, fill) can be logged as a step.
Screenshots & videos: Attachments for failed tests to help debugging.
Metadata: Test duration, environment info, retries, parameters.
History tracking: Compare results across multiple runs.

⚙️ How It Works with Playwright
1. Install Allure dependencies:

bash
npm install --save-dev allure-playwright
npm install --save-dev allure-commandline

2. Configure Playwright (playwright.config.js):

js
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  reporter: [
    ['line'],
    ['allure-playwright']
  ],
});


3. Run tests:

bash
npx playwright test
This generates raw Allure results in the allure-results folder.

4. Generate the report:

bash
npx allure generate allure-results --clean -o allure-report
npx allure open allure-report


