Git HUB
git config --global user.name "Kunal2026-ctrl"
git config --global user.email "hellolearninghub2026@gmail.com"
git config --list  //Shows all current Git configurations (username, email, editor, etc.).
git init  -- Initializes a new Git repository in the current folder.
git remote add origin https://github.com/Kunal2026-ctrl/playwright_framework
git add .  //Stages all files in the folder for commit. Think of it as “mark these files to be saved.”
git add . or git add tests/smoke/  --- Stage all changes (.) or just a specific folder (tests/smoke/).
git commit -m "Initial playwright framework upload"  // Saves a snapshot of staged files with a message. The message should describe what you changed.
git branch -M main  - //Renames the current branch to main. GitHub uses main as the default branch name.
git push -u origin main  //Uploads your local commits to the remote GitHub repo. -u sets origin main as the default, so later you can just type git push.
// repo are nothing but a folder in git HUB


