for Clone Fetch, Pull
git clone https://github.com/Kunal2026-ctrl/playwright_framework
npx playwright install
npx playwright test
npx playwright test tests/LoginToSauceDemo.spec.js
git add . or git add tests/smoke/
git commit -m "Add this new note file"
git push origin main  -- 

M - Modified  --- file is already existing in git repo
U - Means untracked  -- new file


git status 
git fetch  -- it will bring all the new changes been made
git pull -- give all the code to my local machine




📊 
Comparison
Command                	             What it does	                                    When to use
git push -u origin main	             Pushes branch and sets tracking	                First push of a new branch
git push	                         Pushes to the tracked branch	                    Subsequent pushes after tracking is set


✅ 
Example Workflow
You create a new repo and branch locally.

First push:
bash
git push -u origin main
→ This sets up tracking.

Next time, you only need:
bash
git push